		<tr>
			<td><b>Editor in Chief,&nbsp;Recycling Today Media Group</b></td>
		</tr>
		
		
		<tr>
			<td><br><img src=/shared_files/techspeakers_photos/Taylor_Brian.jpg align=left valign="top">&nbsp;Brian Taylor, who joined the Recycling Today Media Group in September of 1997 as a managing editor, now serves as editor in chief of the group.<br><br>
The Recycling Today Media Group, based in Richfield, Ohio, is part of GIE Media Inc. The Group’s stable of recycling industry products includes the monthly periodical <i>Recycling Today</i>; the bi-monthly periodical <i>Construction & Demolition Recycling</i>; the bi-monthly periodical <i>Secure Destruction Business</i>; the annual <i>Paper Recycling Markets Directory</i>; the annual <i>North American Scrap Metals Directory</i>; and the recycling industry’s most comprehensive news Web sites: www.RecyclingToday.com, www.SDBmagazine.com and www.CDRecycler.com. The Media Group also hosts several annual industry conferences, including the Electronics Recycling Conference, taking place in Chicago June 22-24, 2008.<br><br>
Taylor, a graduate of the University of Toledo and a lifelong Ohioan, has been a business journalist for 20 years. His work for <i>Recycling Today</i> involves tracking the value, supply and demand of recyclable commodities including metals, paper, plastics, concrete and wood. As the editor-in-chief of each of the Media Group’s publications, he also gathers information on equipment, processing technologies and emerging end markets for recyclables, and helps assemble databases of critical scrap and recycling industry information.</td>
		
		
